{"title_page": "Casey Wittenberg", "text_new": "{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Casey Wittenberg\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = \n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1984|11|30}}\n| birth_place       = [[Memphis, Tennessee]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1984|11|30}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n| weight            = {{convert|158|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| nationality       = {{USA}}\n| residence         = \n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = [[Oklahoma State University]]\n| yearpro           = 2004\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[Web.com Tour]]\n| extour            = [[PGA Tour]]\n| prowins           = 6\n| pgawins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour wins -->\n| eurowins          = <!-- Number of European Tour wins -->\n| japwins           = <!-- Number of Japan Golf Tour wins -->\n| asiawins          = <!-- Number of Asian Tour wins -->\n| sunwins           = <!-- Number of Sunshine Tour wins -->\n| auswins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour of Australasia wins -->\n| nwidewins         = 3\n| chalwins          = <!-- Number of Challenge Tour wins -->\n| champwins         = <!-- Number of Champions Tour wins -->\n| seneurowins       = <!-- Number of European Seniors Tour wins -->\n| otherwins         = 3\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| masters           = T13: 2004\n| usopen            = T10: [[2012 U.S. Open (golf)|2012]]\n| open              = DNP\n| pga               = DNP\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year|Web.com Tour<br>leading money winner]]\n| year1             = 2012\n| award2            = [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year|Web.com Tour<br>Player of the Year]]\n| year2             = 2012\n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Casey Wittenberg''' (born November 30, 1984) is an American [[professional golfer]] who had a successful amateur career.\n\nWittenberg was born in [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. He played collegiately at [[Oklahoma State University]]. He lost to [[Nick Flanagan]] in the finals of the 2003 [[U.S. Amateur]].\n\nIn 2004, he finished 13th at the [[Masters Tournament]], the lowest amateur finish in 41 years. He was the only player in the field to improve his score each round. Additionally, he registered the lowest Sunday back 9 score (31) of any amateur in Masters history.\n\nAt the 2004 [[U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]] at [[Shinnecock Hills Golf Club|Shinnecock Hills]], he shot a four round total of 296, which was the second best of any amateur in the tournament that year.<ref>[http://www.golfgearreview.com/article-display/1008.html Callaway Golf Signs Rising Young Star Casey Wittenberg to Endorse Company's Golf Clubs and Golf Balls] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090106053939/http://www.golfgearreview.com/article-display/1008.html |date=January 6, 2009 }}</ref>\n\nWittenberg turned professional in 2004 and played on the [[PGA Tour]], [[Web.com Tour]] (formerly Nationwide Tour), and mini-tours since. In 2012, Wittenberg won his first title on a major golf tour, the Nationwide Tour's [[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]]. He followed it up three months later with his second win of the season at the [[Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open]], one week after finishing T10 at the [[2012 U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]].\n\nWittenberg was the leading money winner on the Web.com Tour in 2012, earning his 2013 PGA Tour card, and was named [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year]]. In 2013, he made only eight cut in 27 tournaments and finished 150th on the money list and 164th on the [[FedEx Cup]] points list, resulting in the loss of his PGA Tour card.\n\nWittenberg returned to the Web.com Tour in [[2014 Web.com Tour|2014]] and has played there since. He won again in [[2017 Web.com Tour|2017]] at the [[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]], but he finished the regular season points in 41st and once again failed to earn his PGA Tour card.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pgatour.com/webcom/stats/stat.02668.2017.html |title=2017 Web.com Tour Regular Season Points List |publisher=PGA Tour |date=December 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Amateur wins (4)==\n''this list may be incomplete''\n*2001 [[Azalea Invitational]]\n*2003 [[Southern Amateur]], [[Porter Cup]], [[Terra Cotta Invitational]]\n\n==Professional wins (6)==\n===Web.com Tour wins (3)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runners-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=right|Mar 25, [[2012 Nationwide Tour|2012]]\n|[[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]]\n|\u221224 (66-66-63-65=260)\n|8 strokes\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Paul Claxton]], {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Fabi\u00e1n G\u00f3mez]],<br>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Chris Riley (golfer)|Chris Riley]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=right|Jun 24, 2012\n|[[Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open]]\n|\u221218 (63-70-67-66=266)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Jim Herman]], {{flagicon|USA}} [[Justin Hicks]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|align=right|Mar 26, [[2017 Web.com Tour|2017]]\n|[[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]] <small>(2)</small>\n|\u221221 (65-64-65-69=263)\n|3 strokes\n|{{flagicon|CHN}} [[Zhang Xinjun]]\n|}\n\n===NGA Hooters Tour wins (3)===\n*2006 Pearl River Resort Golf Classic\n*2007 Kandy Waters Memorial Classic, Flora Bama Lounge Classic\n\n==Results in major championships==\n{| cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 95%; border: #aaa solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"\n!align=\"left\"|Tournament\n!2004\n!2005\n!2006\n!2007\n!2008\n!2009\n!2010\n!2011\n!2012\n!2013\n!2014\n|-\n|align=left|[[Masters Tournament]]\n|T13 <span style=\"font-size:87%;\">LA</span>\n|T33\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|-\n|align=left|[[U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]]\n|T36\n|CUT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|CUT\n|CUT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:yellow;\"|T10\n|CUT\n|CUT\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Open Championship]]\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|-\n|align=left|[[PGA Championship]]\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|}\n{{legend|yellow|Top 10}}\n{{legend|#eeeeee|Did not play}}\n<span style=\"font-size:87%;\">LA</span> = Low amateur<br/>\nCUT = missed the half-way cut<br />\n\"T\" indicates a tie for a place\n\n==U.S. national team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Junior Ryder Cup]]: 2002\n*[[Walker Cup]]: [[2003 Walker Cup|2003]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[2008 Nationwide Tour graduates]]\n*[[2012 Web.com Tour graduates]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{PGATour player|26497}}\n*{{OWGR|8819}}\n*[https://archive.is/20130105000026/http://www.ngahooters.tourgolfscores.com/public/standings/player_stats.cfm?pcid=609&yearID=&tid= Results and statistics on the NGA Hooters Tour's official site]\n\n{{Web.com Tour Player of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wittenberg, Casey}}\n[[Category:American male golfers]]\n[[Category:Oklahoma State Cowboys golfers]]\n[[Category:PGA Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:Korn Ferry Tour graduates]]\n[[Category:Golfers from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Memphis, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Casey Wittenberg\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = \n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1984|11|30}}\n| birth_place       = [[Memphis, Tennessee]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1984|11|30}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n| weight            = {{convert|158|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| nationality       = {{USA}}\n| residence         = \n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = [[Oklahoma State University]]\n| yearpro           = 2004\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[Web.com Tour]]\n| extour            = [[PGA Tour]]\n| prowins           = 6\n| pgawins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour wins -->\n| eurowins          = <!-- Number of European Tour wins -->\n| japwins           = <!-- Number of Japan Golf Tour wins -->\n| asiawins          = <!-- Number of Asian Tour wins -->\n| sunwins           = <!-- Number of Sunshine Tour wins -->\n| auswins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour of Australasia wins -->\n| nwidewins         = 3\n| chalwins          = <!-- Number of Challenge Tour wins -->\n| champwins         = <!-- Number of Champions Tour wins -->\n| seneurowins       = <!-- Number of European Seniors Tour wins -->\n| otherwins         = 3\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| masters           = T13: 2004\n| usopen            = T10: [[2012 U.S. Open (golf)|2012]]\n| open              = DNP\n| pga               = DNP\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year|Web.com Tour<br>leading money winner]]\n| year1             = 2012\n| award2            = [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year|Web.com Tour<br>Player of the Year]]\n| year2             = 2012\n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Casey Wittenberg''' (born November 30, 1984) is an American [[professional golfer]] who had a successful amateur career.\n\nWittenberg was born in [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. He played collegiately at [[Oklahoma State University]]. He lost to [[Nick Flanagan]] in the finals of the 2003 [[U.S. Amateur]].\n\nIn 2004, he finished 13th at the [[Masters Tournament]], the lowest amateur finish in 41 years. He was the only player in the field to improve his score each round. Additionally, he registered the lowest Sunday back 9 score (31) of any amateur in Masters history.\n\nAt the 2004 [[U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]] at [[Shinnecock Hills Golf Club|Shinnecock Hills]], he shot a four round total of 296, which was the second best of any amateur in the tournament that year.<ref>[http://www.golfgearreview.com/article-display/1008.html Callaway Golf Signs Rising Young Star Casey Wittenberg to Endorse Company's Golf Clubs and Golf Balls] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090106053939/http://www.golfgearreview.com/article-display/1008.html |date=January 6, 2009 }}</ref>\n\nWittenberg turned professional in 2004 and has played on the [[PGA Tour]], [[Web.com Tour]] (formerly Nationwide Tour), and mini-tours since. In 2012, Wittenberg won his first title on a major golf tour, the Nationwide Tour's [[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]]. He followed it up three months later with his second win of the season at the [[Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open]], one week after finishing T10 at the [[2012 U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]].\n\nWittenberg was the leading money winner on the Web.com Tour in 2012, earning him his 2013 PGA Tour card, and was named [[Web.com Tour Player of the Year]]. In 2013, he made only eight cut in 27 tournaments and finished 150th on the money list and 164th on the [[FedEx Cup]] points list, losing his PGA Tour card.\n\nWittenberg returned to the Web.com Tour in [[2014 Web.com Tour|2014]] and has played there since. He did win again in [[2017 Web.com Tour|2017]] at the [[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]], but he finished the regular season points in 41st and once again failed to earn his PGA Tour card.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pgatour.com/webcom/stats/stat.02668.2017.html |title=2017 Web.com Tour Regular Season Points List |publisher=PGA Tour |date=December 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Amateur wins (4)==\n''this list may be incomplete''\n*2001 [[Azalea Invitational]]\n*2003 [[Southern Amateur]], [[Porter Cup]], [[Terra Cotta Invitational]]\n\n==Professional wins (6)==\n===Web.com Tour wins (3)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runners-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=right|Mar 25, [[2012 Nationwide Tour|2012]]\n|[[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]]\n|\u221224 (66-66-63-65=260)\n|8 strokes\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Paul Claxton]], {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Fabi\u00e1n G\u00f3mez]],<br>{{flagicon|USA}} [[Chris Riley (golfer)|Chris Riley]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=right|Jun 24, 2012\n|[[Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open]]\n|\u221218 (63-70-67-66=266)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Jim Herman]], {{flagicon|USA}} [[Justin Hicks]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|align=right|Mar 26, [[2017 Web.com Tour|2017]]\n|[[Chitimacha Louisiana Open]] <small>(2)</small>\n|\u221221 (65-