| publisher  = Capcom\n| director   = {{Unbulleted list|Kazunori Kadoi|Yasuhiro Anpo}}\n| producer   = {{Unbulleted list|Yoshiaki Hirabayashi|Tsuyoshi Kanda}}\n| designer   = Hidehiro Goda\n| programmer = Masatoshi Fukazawa\n| artist     = {{Unbulleted list|Gez Fry|Satoshi Takamatsu}}\n| composer   = {{Unbulleted list|Shusaku Uchiyama|Zhenlan Kang}}<!--Lead composers only, as per template documentation. -->\n| series     = ''[[Resident Evil]]''\n| engine     = <!--Wikidata-->\n| platforms  = {{Unbulleted list|[[Windows]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]}}\n| released   = January 25, 2019\n| genre      = [[Survival horror]]\n| modes      = [[Single-player]]\n}}\n'''''Resident Evil 2'''''{{efn|{{nihongo|Known in Japan as '''''Biohazard RE:2'''''|\u30d0\u30a4\u30aa\u30cf\u30b6\u30fc\u30c9 RE:2|Baiohaz\u0101do \u0100ru \u012a Ts\u016b|lead=yes}} and commonly referred to as '''''Resident Evil 2 Remake''''' to differentiate from the original.}} is a [[survival horror]] game developed and published by [[Capcom]]. A [[Video game remake|remake]] of the 1998 game [[Resident Evil 2|''Resident Evil 2'']], it was released for [[Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on January 25, 2019. Players control rookie police officer [[Leon S. Kennedy]] and student [[Claire Redfield]] as they attempt to escape Raccoon City during a [[zombie apocalypse]].  \n\nCapcom considered remaking ''Resident Evil 2'' following the successful release of [[Resident Evil (2002 video game)|the remake of the first ''Resident Evil'']] in 2002. It was delayed as series creator [[Shinji Mikami]] did not want to divert development from ''[[Resident Evil 4]]'' (2005). Capcom announced the ''Resident Evil 2'' remake in August 2015, and released the first trailer and gameplay footage at [[E3 2018]].\n\n''Resident Evil 2'' received acclaim, with praise for its presentation, gameplay, and faithfulness to the original. It was nominated for several awards, including numerous [[game of the year|\"game of the year]]\" awards. By December 2019, it had sold over 5.8 million copies, outselling the original.\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Resident Evil 2 Remake gameplay.png|left|thumb|[[Claire Redfield]] is one of the game's two main playable characters.]]\n''Resident Evil 2'' is a remake of the 1998 game [[Resident Evil 2|of the same name]]. Unlike the original, which uses [[tank controls]] and fixed camera angles, the re-imagining features \"over-the-shoulder\" [[third-person shooter]] gameplay similar to ''[[Resident Evil&nbsp;4]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/e3-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-is-familiar-but-ter/1100-6459801/|title=E3 2018: Resident Evil 2 Remake Is Familiar But Terrifying In New Ways|last=Espineli|first=Matt|date=June 12, 2018|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613084807/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/e3-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-is-familiar-but-ter/1100-6459801/|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, the standard difficulty mode allows players to save as often as they would like inside safe rooms. If the player chooses to play on \"Hardcore\" difficulty, players will be required to collect and use a finite number of ink ribbons to save the game's progress, much like in the original game.\n\nAs with the original game, the remake of ''Resident Evil 2'' offers the option to play through the main campaign with one of two protagonists, the rookie cop [[Leon S. Kennedy]] or the college student [[Claire Redfield]]. Depending on the player's choice, the main story will be experienced with variations in subplots, accessible areas, and obtainable items.\n\nSimilar to the \"Scenario B\" feature of the original game, beating the main campaign for the first time unlocks the option to play through a \"2nd Run\" as the other protagonist. 2nd Run is a variation of the main campaign that adds additional content to frame the second playthrough as occurring concurrently with the first playthrough. For example, the protagonist in 2nd Run will enter the police station from a different entrance and find several doors already unlocked by the protagonist from the first playthrough. Completing 2nd Run is also required to experience the true ending of the main campaign.\n\n== Plot ==\n{{Long plot|date=March 2020}}\nThe game is set in Raccoon City in September 1998, two months after the events of ''[[Resident Evil (2002 video game)|Resident Evil]]''. Most of the citizens have been turned into mindless creatures, referred to by survivors as zombies, due to an outbreak of a viral [[bioweapon]] known as the [[T-Virus]], manufactured by [[Umbrella Corporation]].<ref name=\"characters\">{{cite book|title=Resident Evil Archives|date=November 9, 2005|publisher=[[BradyGames Publishing]]|isbn=0-7440-0655-4|pages=117\u2013121}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Resident Evil Archives|date=November 9, 2005|publisher=[[BradyGames Publishing]]|isbn=0-7440-0655-4|page=253}}</ref> The game begins at a [[gas station]] outside of the city, where rookie police officer [[Leon S. Kennedy]] meets college student [[Claire Redfield]], who is looking for her brother [[Chris Redfield]].\n\nAfter being separated following a car accident, Leon and Claire agree to meet up at the city's police department. The building is infested by zombies, and other monsters, including the \"[[Tyrant (Resident Evil)|Tyrant]]\",{{efn|Officially known as T-00, but commonly referred to as \"Mr. X\".}} who is dispatched to hunt down and kill any survivors. The creatures and various obstacles prevent Leon and Claire from actually reuniting as they are forced to find a way to escape the city.\n\n=== Claire scenario ===\nClaire encounters a young girl, Sherry Birkin, who is being pursued by a monstrous creature. The two manage to escape into the police station parking garage, where corrupt Police Chief Brian Irons abducts Sherry, and locks her in an abandoned orphanage. Claire soon receives a call from Irons to trade Sherry for a pendant she had dropped during the abduction, threatening to kill the little girl if Claire does not comply. Reluctantly, Claire agrees to do so.\n\nSherry tries to escape on her own, but is soon cornered by Irons. Before Irons can harm her, the creature that had been chasing Sherry returns and implants Irons with a parasite. Claire arrives to save Sherry, and the parasite bursts out of Irons' chest, killing him. As Claire and Sherry attempt to leave, the Tyrant arrives and chases the pair into an elevator, but is killed by the creature stalking Sherry. The creature then tries to attack Claire and Sherry, but accidentally causes the elevator to fall into the sewers. The resulting impact knocks Claire unconscious, and Sherry is forced to abandon her to escape.\n\nClaire is found by Annette, Sherry's mother. Annette reveals that the creature after Sherry is William, her husband. The Birkins developed the G-Virus for Umbrella; however, William planned to sell it to the U.S. military. Umbrella sent its paramilitary force to confiscate his work, leading to William being fatally shot. To avoid death and vowing revenge, William had injected himself with the G-Virus. The infected William hunted down the Umbrella soldiers in the sewers. During the carnage he shattered vials of the T-virus the troops had taken, infecting sewer rats and indirectly causing the Raccoon City outbreak. Now a mindless mutating beast, the G-Virus drives William to infect Sherry, as she is the closest genetic match to William and thus the most suitable host to spread the infection.\n\nClaire finds Sherry trapped in a trash compactor by Annette. Upon reaching her, however, Sherry falls ill. Annette realizes William has already infected Sherry and has Claire bring her to an Umbrella lab called NEST, where a vaccine is stored. Once there, Claire uses Sherry's pendant to unlock the vaccine, but William attacks. Claire sends Annette to administer the vaccine while she fights William. After seemingly killing him, Claire reunites with Annette, who has managed to cure Sherry before dying from internal injuries. Sherry tearfully bids her mother goodbye. As the facility enacts a self-destruct protocol, Claire and Sherry make their way to an evacuation train. William returns yet again, and Claire defeats him just as the train prepares to leave. Upon boarding, Claire discovers Leon there as well.\n\n=== Leon scenario ===\nLeon is saved from an infected dog by FBI agent, [[Ada Wong]]. They find reporter Ben Bertolucci in the holding cells; imprisoned by Irons for investigating Umbrella. As Ben tries to convince Leon to release him, the Tyrant kills Ben. While attempting to escape the police station, Leon is intercepted by the Tyrant but is again saved by Ada. Leon pledges to help Ada retrieve a G-Virus sample to prove Umbrella's corruption.\n\nIn the sewers, Annette Birkin ambushes the pair and shoots at Ada; Leon takes the bullet and passes out. Ada pursues Annette but is knocked into a trash compactor. Leon rescues her, and they descend to NEST via cable car, where Ada kisses Leon.\n\nAda, injured, requests that Leon obtain the G sample. In Birkin's lab, Leon obtains a sample but is attacked by William. Annette tries to kill him, but is mortally wounded. Leon defeats William and tends to Annette, who claims that Ada is a mercenary and will sell the virus to the highest bidder.\n\nLeon confronts Ada as the lab's self-destruct protocol begins, where she admits to being a mercenary. Ada demands the G-Virus sample from Leon at gunpoint, but Annette shoots Ada before succumbing to her injuries. As Ada falls off the bridge; Leon catches her, letting the virus sample fall into the abyss. Leon loses his grip and Ada falls.\n\nAs Leon attempts to escape the lab, he is ambushed by the Tyrant, now transformed into the larger and more powerful Super Tyrant and engages it in a final battle. Ada, having survived the fall, tosses a rocket launcher to him, which Leon uses to finally destroy the Super Tyrant. Leon boards the evacuation train, discovering Claire and Sherry already aboard.\n\n=== Ending ===\nAfter Leon, Claire, and Sherry reunite, William attacks the train, having mutated into a gigantic putrid mass of fangs and flesh. Claire and Leon are almost killed in the fight, but manage to uncouple the carriage occupied by William. The carriage falls behind and is consumed by the exploding lab, destroying William once and for all. As the three survivors finally escape Raccoon City, they vow to continue the fight against Umbrella.\n\n== Development ==\n[[File:Resident Evil 2 police car at E3 2018.jpg|thumb|Promotional booth at [[E3 2018]]]]\nThe original ''[[Resident Evil 2]]'' was released for the PlayStation in 1998. Following the release of the [[Resident Evil (2002 video game)|2002 remake of the first ''Resident Evil'']] for the [[GameCube]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/interview/2008/vol01/index.html|title=Developer Interview 2008: vol01.Jun Takeuchi|date=September 30, 2008|publisher=[[Capcom Co., Ltd]]|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wKKUD5nb?url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/interview/2008/vol01/index.html|archivedate=February 7, 2011|url-status=dead|accessdate=February 7, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/resident-evil-5_0_7?page=2|title=Resident Evil 5 Xbox 360 Hands On|author=Reed, Kristan|date=November 13, 2008|work=[[Eurogamer.net]]|publisher=Eurogamer Network Ltd|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wGky94At?url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/resident-evil-5_0_7?page=2|archivedate=February 5, 2011|url-status=live|accessdate=February 5, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gametrailers.com/video/jun-takeuchi-resident-evil/46044|title=Jun Takeuchi Interview II|date=February 27, 2009|work=[[GameTrailers]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HcUlTCqy?url=http://www.gametrailers.com/videos/v7g5vi/resident-evil-5-jun-takeuchi-interview-ii|archivedate=June 24, 2013|url-status=live|accessdate=February 5, 2011}}</ref> Capcom considered a similar remake of ''Resident Evil 2'', but series creator [[Shinji Mikami]] did not want to divert development away from ''[[Resident Evil 4]]''.<ref>{{cite journal |script-title=ja:\u4e09\u4e26\u9054\u4e5f\u00d7\u4e09\u4e0a\u771f\u53f8 \u72ec\u5360\u5bfe\u8ac7 |journal=\u30cf\u30a4\u30d1\u30fc\u30ab\u30d7\u30b3\u30f3\u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb |date=June 11, 2002 |publisher=Sony Magazines Inc. |language=Japanese}}</ref> In August 2015, producer Yoshiaki Hirabayashi announced in a video that the remake had been approved and was in active development, ending the video with the phrase \"We Do It\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Senior|first1=Tom|title=Resident Evil 2 Remake is in development|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/resident-evil-2-remake-is-in-development/|website=PC Gamer|accessdate=January 25, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125134449/http://www.pcgamer.com/resident-evil-2-remake-is-in-development/|archivedate=January 25, 2018}}</ref> No further details were released until Sony's [[E3 2018]] press conference, when Capcom released the debut trailer and gameplay footage and removed \"Remake\" from the title.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Resident Evil 2 remake revealed, coming January 2019 |url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/11/17443046/resident-evil-2-remake-trailer-release-date-e3-2018 |website=Polygon |accessdate=June 12, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143127/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/11/17443046/resident-evil-2-remake-trailer-release-date-e3-2018 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Romano |first1=Sal |title=Resident Evil 2 announced for PS4, Xbox One, and PC |url=https://gematsu.com/2018/06/resident-evil-2-announced-ps4-xbox-one-pc |website=Gematsu |accessdate=June 12, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612024124/https://gematsu.com/2018/06/resident-evil-2-announced-ps4-xbox-one-pc |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Hideki Kamiya]], director of the original ''Resident Evil 2'', said that he had pushed Capcom to create a remake for years.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McWhertor |first1=Michael |title=Original Resident Evil 2 director says he pestered Capcom for a remake |url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/6/20/11982568/resident-evil-2-remake-director-hideki-kamiya-capcom |website=Polygon |accessdate=September 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904084535/https://www.polygon.com/2016/6/20/11982568/resident-evil-2-remake-director-hideki-kamiya-capcom |archive-date=September 4, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Hirabayashi said the team was striving to capture the spirit of the original game, and that the team incorporated feedback received about ''[[Resident Evil 6]]'', a game he also produced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.videogamer.com/news/resident-evil-2-remake-progressing-resi-6-feedback-being-taken-on-board-says-producer|title=Resident Evil 2 Remake 'progressing'; Resi 6 feedback being 'taken on board', says producer - VideoGamer.com|access-date=September 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123130416/https://www.videogamer.com/news/resident-evil-2-remake-progressing-resi-6-feedback-being-taken-on-board-says-producer|archive-date=November 23, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTo meet modern expectations, the team decided to alter some character designs to better match the more photorealistic setting; for example, Leon no longer wears large shoulder pads, which were added to distinguish his original, low-polygon model. Ada Wong's red dress was dropped in favor of a trenchcoat with sunglasses for similar reasons. Though they strove to make a \"modern, accessible\" game, they focused on horror over action, hoping to preserve a [[claustrophobia|claustrophobic]] feel.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.polygon.com/interviews/2018/10/8/17911258/resident-evil-2-remakes-changes-additions-new-interview|title=How Capcom updated Resident Evil 2 for 2019|work=Polygon|accessdate=October 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120192112/https://www.polygon.com/interviews/2018/10/8/17911258/resident-evil-2-remakes-changes-additions-new-interview|archive-date=November 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The game uses the RE Engine, the same [[game engine]] used for ''[[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]'', which allowed for Capcom to modernize the gameplay.<ref name=\"e32018announce\"/> Producer Tsuyoshi Kanda acknowledged the difficulty of making zombies seem scary and threatening, as they had become ubiquitous in entertainment media since the release of the original ''[[Resident Evil (1996 video game)|Resident Evil]]'' in 1996.<ref name=\":0\" /> By removing the fixed camera angles, the team had to use different ways to conceal enemies, using elements such as room layout, lighting, and smoke.<ref name=\":0\" /> The new camera system also affected the sound design, as it no longer made sense for sound to come from a fixed source.<ref name=\":0\" /> The faces of several character models are based on scans of real people. Leon S. Kennedy is based on model Eduard Badaluta, Claire Redfield is based on model Jordan McEwen, and Marvin Branagh is based on music producer Patrick Levar.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ashcraft |first1=Brian |title=The Faces Behind Resident Evil 2's Remake Characters |url=https://kotaku.com/the-faces-behind-resident-evil-2s-remake-characters-1827440505 |accessdate=January 21, 2019 |work=[[Kotaku]] |date=July 9, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123000716/https://kotaku.com/the-faces-behind-resident-evil-2s-remake-characters-1827440505 |archive-date=January 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe game features a [[Dolby Atmos]] soundtrack.<ref>https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2017/11/13/xbox-one-x-windows-sonic-dolby-atmos-feature/</ref>\n\n''Resident Evil 2'' was released on [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Windows]] worldwide on January 25, 2019.<ref name=\"e32018announce\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/06/12/e3-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-release-date-announced|title=E3 2018: Resident Evil 2 Remake Release Date Announced|last=Osborn|first=Alex|date=June 11, 2018|website=IGN|language=en-US|accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612152506/http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/06/12/e3-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-release-date-announced|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The game supports enhancements on the [[PlayStation 4 Pro]] and [[Xbox One X]], offering either [[4K resolution]] or 60 [[frames per second]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cryer |first1=Hirun |last2=Orry |first2=Tom |title=Resident Evil 2 Remake Release Date, Gameplay Footage, 4K/60FPS, PC System Specs - Everything we Know |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/13-07-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-release-date |website=USGamer |accessdate=July 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713205152/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/13-07-2018-resident-evil-2-remake-release-date |archive-date=July 13, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> A [[game demo|demo]] known as the ''1-Shot Demo'' was released on January 11, 2019. It ends after 30 minutes and does not allow repeat playthroughs, however the same demo would later be rereleased as the \"R.P.D. Demo\" and does allow repeat playthroughs.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Watts |first1=Steve |title=Resident Evil 2 1-Shot Demo Out Now For Some |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-2-1-shot-demo-out-now-for-some/1100-6464323/ |website=GameSpot |accessdate=January 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Jeffrey |first1=Cal |title=How to play the Resident Evil 2 One-Shot demo more than once |url=https://www.techspot.com/news/78286-how-play-resident-evil-2-one-shot-demo.html |website=Techspot |accessdate=January 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116030321/https://www.techspot.com/news/78286-how-play-resident-evil-2-one-shot-demo.html |archive-date=January 16, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A [[downloadable content]] game mode, known as ''Ghost Survivors'', was released on February 15, 2019.<ref name=\"SC\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2019/02/13/resident-evil-2-the-ghost-survivors-dlc-will-behave-like-the-4th-survivor-and-the-tofu-survivor/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=February 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214174513/https://www.siliconera.com/2019/02/13/resident-evil-2-the-ghost-survivors-dlc-will-behave-like-the-4th-survivor-and-the-tofu-survivor/ |archive-date=February 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gamerevolution.com/guides/497475-resident-evil-2-the-ghost-survivors-4th-scenario-no-way-out-unlock-secret |title=Archived copy |access-date=February 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227182037/https://www.gamerevolution.com/guides/497475-resident-evil-2-the-ghost-survivors-4th-scenario-no-way-out-unlock-secret |archive-date=February 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{Clr}}\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (PC) 89/100<ref name=\"MCPC\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/resident-evil-2 |title=Resident Evil 2 for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531155715/https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/resident-evil-2 |archive-date=May 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><br />(PS4) 91/100<ref name=\"MCPS4\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/resident-evil-2 |title=Resident Evil 2 for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=March 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531155848/https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/resident-evil-2 |archive-date=May 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><br />(XONE) 93/100<ref name=\"MCXONE\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/resident-evil-2|title=Resident Evil 2 for Xbox One Reviews|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=January 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531155947/https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/resident-evil-2|archive-date=May 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Destruct = 9/10<ref name=\"Destruct\">{{cite web |last=Carter |first=Chris |date=January 22, 2019 |url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-resident-evil-2-2019--538881.phtml |title=Review: Resident Evil 2 (2019) |website=[[Destructoid]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124044407/https://www.destructoid.com/review-resident-evil-2-2019--538881.phtml |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| EGM = 9.5/10<ref>{{cite web |last1=Patterson |first1=Mollie L. |title=Resident Evil 2 review |url=http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/resident-evil-2-review/ |website=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly|EGM]] |date=January 22, 2019 |accessdate=January 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130221952/http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/resident-evil-2-review/ |archive-date=January 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Fam = 37/40<ref>{{cite web |title=Famitsu review scores (1/15/19) |url=https://nintendoeverything.com/famitsu-review-scores-1-15-19/ |website=Nintendo Everything |date=January 15, 2019 |accessdate=January 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124044313/https://nintendoeverything.com/famitsu-review-scores-1-15-19/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| GI = 9.5/10<ref name=\"GI\">{{cite web |last=Reeves |first=Ben |date=January 22, 2019 |url=https://www.gameinformer.com/Resident%20Evil%202%20game%20informer%20Review |title=Resident Evil 2 Review |website=[[Game Informer]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124045039/https://www.gameinformer.com/Resident%20Evil%202%20game%20informer%20Review |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| GameRev = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Resident Evil 2 remake review {{!}} The perfect Resi game? |url=https://www.gamerevolution.com/review/485467-resident-evil-2-remake-review-ps4-xbox-one-pc |website=[[Game Revolution]] |date=January 22, 2019 |accessdate=January 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130220854/https://www.gamerevolution.com/review/485467-resident-evil-2-remake-review-ps4-xbox-one-pc |archive-date=January 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| GSpot = 9/10<ref name=\"GSpot\">{{cite web |last=Fillari |first=Alessandro |date=January 22, 2019 |title=Resident Evil 2 Review - Raccoon City Revisited |url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/resident-evil-2-review-raccoon-city-revisited/1900-6417071/ |website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124044753/https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/resident-evil-2-review-revisiting-raccoon-city/1900-6417071/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| IGN = 9.0/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Hatfield |first=Daemon |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |title=Resident Evil 2 Review |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/22/resident-evil-2-review |website=[[IGN]] |date=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124045232/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/22/resident-evil-2-review |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| USG = 4.5/5<ref name=\"USGamer\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/resident-evil-2-review|title=Resident Evil 2 Review|last=Kim|first=Matt|date=January 22, 2019|website=USgamer|language=en|access-date=January 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123225054/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/resident-evil-2-review|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\nFollowing its E3 2018 showing, ''Resident Evil 2'' won the \"Best of Show\" award at the 2018 [[Game Critics Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fogel |first1=Stefanie |title=Game Critics Awards 2018 Names \u2018Resident Evil 2\u2019 Remake Best of Show |url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/game-critics-awards-2018-winners-1202863599/ |website=Variety |accessdate=July 12, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180816173408/https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/game-critics-awards-2018-winners-1202863599/ |archive-date=August 16, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The ''1-Shot Demo'' received over 4.7{{nbsp}}million downloads worldwide.<ref name=\"capcom-sales\">{{cite news |title=Resident Evil 2 Ships 3 Million Units Worldwide in First Week of Sales! |url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/news/html/e190129.html |accessdate=January 29, 2019 |publisher=[[Capcom]] |date=January 29, 2019 |language=ja |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190208132922/http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/news/html/e190129.html |archive-date=February 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''Resident Evil 2'' received \"universal acclaim\" for the PlayStation 4 and Xbox One versions, and \"generally favorable reviews\" for the PC according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPC\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4\"/><ref name=\"MCXONE\"/>\n\n''[[Game Informer]]'' said that \"''Resident Evil 2'' not only looks great, it plays well, and it forces you into a series of dark encounters that are a total rush.\"<ref name=\"GI\"/> ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that it was \"a reminder of how beautifully crafted survival horror games were in their heyday.\"<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web |last=Stuart |first=Keith |date=January 22, 2019 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/games/2019/jan/22/resident-evil-2-review-genre-defining-horror-loaded-with-dread |title=Resident Evil 2 review \u2013 genre-defining horror, loaded with dread |website=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124045704/https://www.theguardian.com/games/2019/jan/22/resident-evil-2-review-genre-defining-horror-loaded-with-dread |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' described it as a \"thrilling return to the legacy of the 1998 original\".<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite web |last=Hoggins |first=Tom |date=January 22, 2019 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/reviews/resident-evil-2-remake-review-survival-horror-perfection/ |title=Resident Evil 2 remake review: Survival horror perfection |website=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124045536/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/reviews/resident-evil-2-remake-review-survival-horror-perfection/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''[[IGN]]'' originally gave the game an 8.8 in their review, only to increase it to a 9.0 after being made aware of the unlockable second playthrough that presents the story from another point of view. They stated in their review that \"Capcom did a fantastic job of resurrecting all the best parts of the classic ''Resident Evil 2'' and making it look, sound, and play like a 2019 game.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/22/resident-evil-2-review|title=Resident Evil 2 review|website=[[IGN]]|first=Daemon|last=Hatfield|date=January 22, 2019|accessdate=January 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124045232/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/01/22/resident-evil-2-review|archive-date=January 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''[[Destructoid]]'' called it \"A hallmark of excellence. There may be flaws, but they are negligible and won't cause massive damage.\"<ref name=\"Destruct\"/> ''[[Eurogamer]]'' described it as \"a masterly reimagining of a modern classic\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-01-22-resident-evil-2-review|title=Resident Evil 2 review - a masterly reimagining of a modern classic|website=[[Eurogamer]]|first=Aoife|last=Wilson|date=January 22, 2019|accessdate=January 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123042417/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2019-01-22-resident-evil-2-review|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]'' said ''Resident Evil 2'' showcases \"the very best of survival horror\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/reviews/2019/1/22/18192509/resident-evil-2-remake-review|title=Resident Evil 2 is everything a video game remake should be|last=McWhertor|first=Michael|date=January 22, 2019|website=Polygon|access-date=January 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123223614/https://www.polygon.com/reviews/2019/1/22/18192509/resident-evil-2-remake-review|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> while ''[[Kotaku]]'' also gave it similar praise, saying it \"provides some of the best moments in the franchise\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/resident-evil-2-the-kotaku-review-1831951036|title=Resident Evil 2: The Kotaku Review|last=Alexandra|first=Heather|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=January 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123005247/https://kotaku.com/resident-evil-2-the-kotaku-review-1831951036|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[GameSpot]]'' said that with ''Resident Evil 2'', \"the classic survival horror franchise embraces its past in a new, exciting way\".<ref name=\"GSpot\"/>\n\n===Sales===\nThe game shipped three{{nbsp}}million copies worldwide in its first week of sales, rising to four million within a month with over one million on PC.<ref name=\"capcom-sales\"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |title=Resident Evil 2 first week shipments top three million |url=https://gematsu.com/2019/01/resident-evil-2-first-week-shipments-top-three-million |website=Gematsu |date=January 29, 2019 |accessdate=January 29, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190129181446/https://gematsu.com/2019/01/resident-evil-2-first-week-shipments-top-three-million |archive-date=January 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Makuch |first=Eddie |title=Resident Evil 2 Remake Sales Hit A New Milestone |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-2-remake-sales-hit-a-new-milestone/1100-6465220/ |website=[[GameSpot]] |date=March 1, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210155110/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-2-remake-sales-hit-a-new-milestone/1100-6465220/ |archive-date=December 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Moyse |first=Chris |title=Resident Evil 2 pops one million sales on PC |url=https://www.destructoid.com/resident-evil-2-pops-one-million-sales-on-pc-546769.phtml |website=[[Destructoid]] |date=March 18, 2019 |accessdate=March 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330063833/https://www.destructoid.com/resident-evil-2-pops-one-million-sales-on-pc-546769.phtml |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> It became Capcom's second biggest launch on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] after ''[[Monster Hunter: World]]'' from 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last=Jones |first=Ali |title=Resident Evil 2 is Capcom\u2019s second-best Steam launch ever |url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/resident-evil-2/resident-evil-2-sales |website=[[PCGamesN]] |date=January 25, 2019 |accessdate=January 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190126045755/https://www.pcgamesn.com/resident-evil-2/resident-evil-2-sales |archive-date=January 26, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''Resident Evil 2'' debuted at number two on the Japanese charts with 252,848 retail sales, after ''[[Kingdom Hearts III]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |title=Media Create Sales: 1/21/19 \u2013 1/27/19 |url=https://gematsu.com/2019/01/media-create-sales-1-21-19-1-27-19|website=Gematsu |date=January 30, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2019  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130153116/https://gematsu.com/2019/01/media-create-sales-1-21-19-1-27-19 |archive-date=January 30, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u300cKINGDOM HEARTS III\u300d61\u4e07\u672c\uff0c\u300c\u30d0\u30a4\u30aa\u30cf\u30b6\u30fc\u30c9 RE:2\u300d25\u4e072000\u672c\u306e\u300c\u9031\u9593\u8ca9\u58f2\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\uff0b\u300d |url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/117/G011794/20190130079/ |work=[[4Gamer.net]] |date=January 30, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2019 |language=Japanese|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201131445/https://www.4gamer.net/games/117/G011794/20190130079/ |archive-date=February 1, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> As of March, the game was still among the top 20 best selling video games in Japan with more than 352,000 sold copies.<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |title=Media Create Sales: 3/4/19 \u2013 3/10/19 |url=https://gematsu.com/2019/03/media-create-sales-3-4-19-3-10-19 |website=Gematsu |date=March 13, 2019 |accessdate=March 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190313185936/https://gematsu.com/2019/03/media-create-sales-3-4-19-3-10-19 |archive-date=March 13, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''Resident Evil 2'' also topped the UK charts, becoming Capcom's biggest UK launch since ''[[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]'' (2017) in physical retail sale, and was the UK's best-selling game in January 2019, despite being available for only two days.<ref>{{cite web |last=Khan |first=Zarmena |title=Resident Evil 2 Was UK Retail\u2019s Best-Selling Game in January 2019 Despite Being on Shelves for 2 Days |url=https://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2019/02/02/resident-evil-2-sales-jan-2019-uk-retail/ |website=[[PlayStation LifeStyle]] |date=February 2, 2019 |accessdate=February 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203052904/https://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2019/02/02/resident-evil-2-sales-jan-2019-uk-retail/ |archive-date=February 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> By December 2019, the game had sold over 5.8 million copies, which was more than the original game.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kerr |first1=Chris |title=Resident Evil 2 remake has passed 5 million sales |url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/355522/Resident_Evil_2_remake_has_passed_5_million_sales.php |website=Gamasutra |accessdate=11 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211214652/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/355522/Resident_Evil_2_remake_has_passed_5_million_sales.php |archive-date=December 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Platinum Titles |url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/finance/million.html |website=[[Capcom]] |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Result !! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Game Critics Awards]]\n| Best of Show\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |last=Watts |first=Steve |title=Resident Evil 2 Wins Top Honor In E3 Game Critics Awards |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-2-wins-top-honor-in-e3-game-critics-/1100-6460135/ |website=GameSpot |date=July 5, 2018 |accessdate=November 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803224106/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/resident-evil-2-wins-top-honor-in-e3-game-critics-/1100-6460135/ |archive-date=August 3, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Console Game\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n| Best Action/Adventure Game\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n| [[Japan Game Awards]]\n| Award for Excellence\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |last=Craddock |first=Ryan |title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Dominates The Japan Game Awards 2019 |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/09/super_smash_bros_ultimate_dominates_the_japan_game_awards_2019 |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |date=September 13, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190913211302/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/09/